<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880928-0075 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: United Technologies Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> UTX </CO><IN> ARO </IN><TEXT>   United Technologies Corp.'s Pratt andamp; Whitney unit said two airlines have ordered more than $150 million in jet engines for new aircraft, if all sales options are exercised.    Singapore Airlines agreed to purchase at least six, and possibly as many as 24, jet engines to power new Airbus Industrie A-310-300 aircraft it has ordered. Deliveries are to begin next year.    Aerovias Nacionales de Colombia S.A., or Avianca, ordered four jet engines plus spares for two Boeing 767 aircraft that it has ordered. The engines are scheduled for delivery in 1989 and 1990. United Technologies, a major manufacturer of aircraft engines, is based in Hartford, Conn. </TEXT></DOC>